? This book tackles three core challenges of performance faced by social enterprises and nonprofit organizations alike: what to measure, what kinds of performance systems to build, and how to align multiple demands for accountability. It lays out four different types of strategies for managers to consider—niche, integrated, emergent, and ecosystem—and details the types of performance measurement and accountability systems best suited to each. Finally, this book examines the roles of funders such as impact investors, philanthropic foundations, and international aid agencies, laying out how they can best enable meaningful performance measurement.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aNonprofit organizationsxEvaluation. 0aOrganizational effectivenessxMeasurement. 0aSocial changexEvaluation. 0aSocial entrepreneurshipxEvaluation. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Nonprofit Organizations & Charities / General.2bisacsh  aaccountability.  acontingency theory.  aimpact investing.  ainternational aid.  anonprofit organization.  aorganizational design.  aperformance measurement.  aphilanthropy.  asocial enterprise.  astrategy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2020 Englishz978311070479208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2020z9783110704624oZDB-23-DBV08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311069228040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360921140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503609211423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503609211.jpg  a978-3-11-069228-0